    <entry>
        <title>Timelapse with an esp32-cam</title>
        <author>
            <name>Rémi Sarrailh</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://en.usini.eu/camera-a-base-desp32/"/>
        <id>https://en.usini.eu/camera-a-base-desp32/</id>

        <updated>2019-06-01T02:19:52+02:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://en.usini.eu/media/posts/11/esp32cam.jpg" alt="" />
                    I was intrigued by this camera which cost 9$ (with shipping cost), and Rui&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <img src="https://en.usini.eu/media/posts/11/esp32cam.jpg" alt="" />
                <p>I was intrigued by this <a href="https://www.aliexpress.com/item/ESP32-CAM-ESP-32S-WiFi-Module-ESP32-serial-to-WiFi-ESP32-CAM-Development-Board-5V-Bluetooth/32992663411.html">camera </a>which cost 9$ (with shipping cost), and <a href="https://randomnerdtutorials.com/">Rui Santos video (Randomnerdtutorials)</a> so I decided to buy it.</p>
<figure class="post__video"><iframe width="560" height="314" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/36p9To2hfak" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" ></iframe></figure>
<div class="channels-Ie2l6A vertical-V37hAW flex-1O1GKY directionColumn-35P_nr">
<div class="messageCozy-2JPAPA message-1PNnaP">
<div class="contentCozy-3XX413 content-3dzVd8">
<div class="containerCozy-336-Cz container-206Blv">
<div class="markup-2BOw-j">After testing it, i let it aside, and when I wanted to show it at my workshop at <a href="https://labsud.org">LabSud</a>, it didn't works. <br><br>I discover that you need to have a good power supply to make it works.<br>If it isn't well powered, the esp32 <strong>will not start or the image will have weird lines.</strong></div>
</div>
<div class="containerCozy-B4noqO container-1e22Ot"> </div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="messageCozy-2JPAPA message-1PNnaP">
<div class="contentCozy-3XX413 content-3dzVd8">
<div class="containerCozy-336-Cz container-206Blv">
<div class="buttonContainer-KtQ8wc">You can find sketchs for it directly inside the Arduino software (when you add ESP32 support)</div>
<div class="buttonContainer-KtQ8wc"><br>Here is a tutorial on how to upload a sketch on it : <a title="https://randomnerdtutorials.com/esp32-cam-video-streaming-face-recognition-arduino-ide/" class="anchor-3Z-8Bb anchorUnderlineOnHover-2ESHQB" href="https://randomnerdtutorials.com/esp32-cam-video-streaming-face-recognition-arduino-ide/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" role="button" tabindex="0">https://randomnerdtutorials.com/esp32-cam-video-streaming-face-recognition-arduino-ide/</a></div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j"> </div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j">You need</div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j">
<ul>
<li class="markup-2BOw-j">a FTDI programmer</li>
<li class="markup-2BOw-j">Connect IO0 with GND to put it in upload mode.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center" ><img src="https://en.usini.eu/media/posts/11/ESP32-CAM-wiring-FTDI1.png" alt="Credits: RandomNerdTutorials.com" width="750" height="310">
<figcaption >Randomnerdtutorials.com</figcaption>
</figure>
<p><strong>Arduino Settings</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="containerCozy-336-Cz container-206Blv">--&gt; ESP32 Wrover in Board <br>--&gt; Huge App (3MB No OTA) in Partition Scheme <br>--&gt; Open ESP32 examples --&gt; Camera --&gt; CameraWebServer</div>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center" ><img src="https://en.usini.eu/media/posts/11/upload-code-esp32-cam.png" alt="Credits : Randomnerdtutorials.com" width="369" height="410">
<figcaption >Randomnerdtutorials.com</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="containerCozy-336-Cz container-206Blv">
<div class="messageCozy-2JPAPA message-1PNnaP">
<div class="contentCozy-3XX413 content-3dzVd8">
<div class="containerCozy-336-Cz container-206Blv">
<div class="markup-2BOw-j">I had a lot of failed upload, probably due to a bad power supply.<br>A computer USB probably doesn't deliver not enough to power it, but if you retry enough it should works (Obviously it should work better if you use an external power supply) </div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j"> </div>
</div>
<div class="containerCozy-B4noqO container-1e22Ot">Here is how the interface looks like, you should even be able to use face recognition, but I didn't manage to make it works.</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="messageCozy-2JPAPA message-1PNnaP">
<div class="contentCozy-3XX413 content-3dzVd8">
<div class="containerCozy-336-Cz container-206Blv">
<figure class="post__image post__image" ><img src="https://en.usini.eu/media/posts/11/ESP32-CAM-video-streaming-example.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="407">
<figcaption >Randomnerdtutorials.com</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j">My goal was to make timelapse, so I needed to find a way to correctly power my esp32cam.</div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j"> </div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j">First I used my <strong>FTDI programmer, but it overheat, bad idea!</strong><br>Looking around, I found Lipo charger module (<a href="https://www.aliexpress.com/item/5-pcs-Micro-USB-5V-1A-18650-TP4056-Lithium-Battery-Charger-Module-Charging-Board-With-Protection/32797834680.html"></a><a href="https://fr.aliexpress.com/item/32489232521.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TP4056)</a>.</div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j"><img class="post__image--center" src="https://en.usini.eu/media/posts/11/tp4056.png" alt="" width="243" height="232"></div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j">Near the micro USB, there are a + / - which supply 5v, the ESP32-cam can takes 5v (which is convert to 3.3v)</div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j">Unfortunately , I forgot to <strong>change the VCC cable from 3.3v to 5v.<br>Thankfully, it didn't damage my board.</strong></div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j"> </div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j">Since I won't use a Lipo battery, I will change it with an <a href="https://www.aliexpress.com/item/10pcs-MICRO-USB-To-DIP-Adapter-5pin-Female-Connector-B-Type-PCB-Converter-Breadboard-USB-01/32867946438.html">USB module</a></div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j"><img class="post__image--center" src="https://en.usini.eu/media/posts/11/alimusb.png" width="217" height="193"></div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j">In order to get the images and save it on my google Drive, I used my media center Raspberry Pi which have <a href="https://github.com/ccrisan/motioneye/wiki">motionEye.</a></div>
<div class="markup-2BOw-j"> </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="containerCozy-B4noqO container-1e22Ot">I added the ESP32 cam stream (http://192.168.x.x:81/stream) on it.</div>
